l-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Marmalead ($19/mo), eRank ($5.99/mo), Alura ($19.99/mo) all bundle scheduled SEO checks; Klaviyo's `Flows` ($45/mo) sends scheduled segmentation reports.\n\n---\n\n### Reappearing seller alert ┬╖ `reappearing-seller-alert` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/reappearing-seller-alert.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`, `web/scrape`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"A quiet competitor just started listing again тАФ heads up before they regain momentum.\" It runs by itself once a week, so you don't have to remember to look.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n- **`web/scrape`**: HTML тЖТ DOM тЖТ main-content extraction тЖТ markdown.\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Marmalead ($19/mo), eRank ($5.99/mo), Alura ($19.99/mo) all bundle scheduled SEO checks; Klaviyo's `Flows` ($45/mo) sends scheduled segmentation reports.\n\n---\n\n### Response-time SLA breach alert ┬╖ `response-time-sla` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/response-time-sla.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/conversa