 тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`sakura/decide`** тАФ Reactive layer (Brooks 1986); same shape as the lowest layer of Simmons's Task Control Architecture.\n- **Category context** тАФ Vendoo ($20тАУ$45/mo) and List Perfectly ($29тАУ$59/mo) sell exactly these Etsy primitives as their core product.\n\n---\n\n### Event-driven carts\n\n*99 carts.*\n\n### Buyer address validator тАФ stop return-to-sender before it ships ┬╖ `address-validation` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/address-validation.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/receipts`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `pii/gate-status`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Validate the buyer address before label print and suggest corrections тАФ RTS prevention.\" It only wakes up when label print requested happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you reply to buyers fast and in your own voice тАФ no canned-AI feel.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`pii/gate-status`**: $g \\in \\{open, closed\\}, \\text{ default } closed$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/receipts`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 receipts.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### After-hours message acknowledgement ┬╖ `after-hours-acknowledge` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/after-hours-acknowledge.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/conversations`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Reply instantly after hours: we got it, will reply by 10am тАФ the no-ghosting promise.\" It only wakes up when conversation received happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you reply to buyers fast and in your own voice тАФ no canned-AI feel.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\nThis cart touches BUYER data so it gates on `pii/gate-status` per Lane-B5 ┬з6; defaults closed.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/conversations`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 conversations.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Apartment unit missing тАФ catch it before the package is lost ┬╖ `apartment-unit-missing` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/apartment-unit-missing.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Shipping address looks like a multi-unit building but has no apartment number тАФ flag before the carrier returns it.\" It only wakes up when new order happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Suggest missing attributes ┬╖ `attribute-fill-suggest` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/etsy/attribute-fill-suggest.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `etsy/listing`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"When a listing is edited, propose the missing taxonomy attributes (material, color, occasion) from the title.\" It only wakes up when listing edited happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`etsy/listing`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/listings/{listing_id}`.\n- **`sakura/decide`** тАФ Reactive layer (Brooks 1986); same shape as the lowest layer of Simmons's Task Control Architecture.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Etsy listing audit тАФ image ┬╖ copy ┬╖ tags ┬╖ price ┬╖ shipping ┬╖ `audit` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/etsy/audit.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/listings`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Fold your listings against an audit axis and surface what needs fixing.\" It only wakes up when axis selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you set prices that won't leave money on the table.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/listings`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/shops/{shop_id}/listings`.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Book ISBN snap тАФ sold comps & condition prompt ┬╖ `book-isbn-snap` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/book-isbn-snap.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `model/fast`, `vision/label`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Snap a book barcode, resolve the ISBN, and surface sold comps with a condition prompt.\" It only wakes up when barcode scan happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `vision/label` тАФ Multi-label tagging of an image (e.g., colours, materials, motifs).\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`vision/label`**: $\\{\\ell: P(\\ell \\mid I) > \\tau\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **`vision/label`** тАФ Google Cloud Vision `LABEL_DETECTION`; Hugging Face Florence-2.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Bulk price % adjust тАФ dry-run, consent, rollback ┬╖ `bulk-price-percent-honest` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/bulk-price-percent-honest.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/listings`, `etsy/reprice`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Apply a % price change across listings тАФ review every diff before anything moves.\" It only wakes up when operator tap happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you set prices that won't leave money on the table.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity.\n\nWrite-class verbs are operator-gated тАФ the cart proposes; the operator approves with a tap.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/listings`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/shops/{shop_id}/listings`.\n- **`etsy/reprice`** тАФ Same shape as Prisync / Repricer.com.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Buyer history snapshot тАФ full order & chat history inline ┬╖ `buyer-history-snapshot` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/buyer-history-snapshot.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/conversations`, `etsy/receipts`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Opening a buyer thread surfaces their full order history and past conversations inline.\" It only wakes up when thread open happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you reply to buyers fast and in your own voice тАФ no canned-AI feel.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\nThis cart touches BUYER data so it gates on `pii/gate-status` per Lane-B5 ┬з6; defaults closed.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/conversations`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 conversations.\n- **`etsy/receipts`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 receipts.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Buyer sentiment watcher ┬╖ `buyer-sentiment-watcher` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/etsy/buyer-sentiment-watcher.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Score the new buyer message for sentiment, surface anything heading negative.\" It only wakes up when new buyer message happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you reply to buyers fast and in your own voice тАФ no canned-AI feel.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`sakura/decide`** тАФ Reactive layer (Brooks 1986); same shape as the lowest layer of Simmons's Task Control Architecture.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Chargeback dispute alert + evidence-gather ┬╖ `chargeback-alert` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/chargeback-alert.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/receipts`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"A chargeback just fired тАФ the system found your order evidence and queued it.\" It only wakes up when chargeback happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/receipts`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 receipts.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Ingest all shop listings into Cortex ┬╖ `cortex-ingest-all-shops` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/cortex-ingest-all-shops.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/remember`, `ebay/listings`, `etsy/listings`, `loam/operator-state`, `meta/products`, `model/fast`, `shopify/products`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Pull every listing from every connected shop into Cortex so edits become Cortex-first.\" It only wakes up when operator initiated happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you put more polish on the words that decide whether a buyer clicks buy.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`ebay/listings`** тАФ eBay Sell API `getInventoryItems`.\n- **`etsy/listings`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/shops/{shop_id}/listings`.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Bulk-publish selected items to every store you choose ┬╖ `cortex-multi-store-publish` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/cortex-multi-store-publish.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `ebay/publish`, `etsy/create-draft`, `loam/operator-state`, `meta/marketplace`, `model/fast`, `shopify/update`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Pick items from Cortex, pick your stores, publish everywhere in one tap.\" It only wakes up when operator initiated happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\nWrite-class verbs are operator-gated тАФ the cart proposes; the operator approves with a tap.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`ebay/publish`** тАФ eBay Sell API `publishOffer`.\n- **`etsy/create-draft`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `POST /shops/{shop_id}/listings`.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Channel-fit filter before multi-store publish ┬╖ `cortex-multi-store-publish-by-channel-fit` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/cortex-multi-store-publish-by-channel-fit.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Filters your items ├Ч stores matrix so only channel-fit items surface before publish.\" It only wakes up when publish requested happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **`sakura/decide`** тАФ Reactive layer (Brooks 1986); same shape as the lowest layer of Simmons's Task Control Architecture.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Publish a collection to every connected store ┬╖ `cortex-multi-store-publish-by-collection` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/cortex-multi-store-publish-by-collection.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `ebay/publish`, `etsy/publish`, `loam/operator-state`, `meta/marketplace`, `shopify/update`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"One tap publishes every item in a Cortex collection across every store you have connected.\" It only wakes up when collection publish tapped happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity.\n\nWrite-class verbs are operator-gated тАФ the cart proposes; the operator approves with a tap.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`ebay/publish`** тАФ eBay Sell API `publishOffer`.\n- **`etsy/publish`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 listing-state PATCH; same shape as the *direct publish* shotgun ([[project_curator_publish_architecture]]).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Publish every tagged item across your stores ┬╖ `cortex-multi-store-publish-by-tag` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/cortex-multi-store-publish-by-tag.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `ebay/publish`, `etsy/publish`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Pick a tag like spring-2026 and push every item under it to your selected stores.\" It only wakes up when tag publish requested happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\nWrite-class verbs are operator-gated тАФ the cart proposes; the operator approves with a tap.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`ebay/publish`** тАФ eBay Sell API `publishOffer`.\n- **`etsy/publish`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 listing-state PATCH; same shape as the *direct publish* shotgun ([[project_curator_publish_architecture]]).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Multi-store publish dry-run тАФ preview before you commit ┬╖ `cortex-multi-store-publish-dry-run` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/cortex-multi-store-publish-dry-run.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"See every listing-create payload across a