ura tells you: \"Connect your YouTube channel so the system can surface cross-platform signals.\" It only wakes up when operator request happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`google/youtube`** тАФ YouTube Data API v3.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Instagram comment stream тАФ live feed ┬╖ `ig-comments-stream` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/ig-comments-stream.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"New Instagram comments arrive live тАФ see what shoppers are saying right now.\" It only wakes up when ig comment happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you keep social posts on-cadence without burning a Sunday on it.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Instagram DM inbox ┬╖ `ig-dm-inbox` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/ig-dm-inbox.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Recent Instagram DMs surfaced from your message thread store.\" It only wakes up when ig webhook happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you reply to buyers fast and in your own voice тАФ no canned-AI feel.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Inventory check тАФ low-stock ┬╖ out-of-stock ┬╖ fast-mover ┬╖ slow-mover ┬╖ `inv` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/etsy/inv.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/inventory`, `etsy/listings`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Parameterized inventory check тАФ axis-filtered listings with reorder hints.\" It only wakes up when inventory check happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you know what to reorder before you run out тАФ and what's collecting dust.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/inventory`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `GET /listings/{listing_id}/inventory`.\n- **`etsy/listings`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/shops/{shop_id}/listings`.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Is-this-still-available DM autoresponder ┬╖ `is-this-still-available-autoreply` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/is-this-still-available-autoreply.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `meta/marketplace`, `meta/products`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Someone asked if it's still available тАФ the system checks and replies instantly.\" It only wakes up when dm received happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you reply to buyers fast and in your own voice тАФ no canned-AI feel.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`meta/marketplace`** тАФ Meta Commerce Manager API.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Per-listing portrait тАФ vitals at a glance ┬╖ `listing-portrait` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/etsy/listing-portrait.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `etsy/listing`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Title, price, views, recent sales, age, and tags for one listing тАФ no AI spend.\" It only wakes up when listing selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you put more polish on the words that decide whether a buyer clicks buy.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`etsy/listing`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/listings/{listing_id}`.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Read a Messenger thread ┬╖ `meta-messenger-read-thread` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/meta-messenger-read-thread.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `meta/dm`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Pull the full message history for one Messenger thread.\" It only wakes up when thread selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\nThis cart touches BUYER data so it gates on `pii/gate-status` per Lane-B5 ┬з6; defaults closed.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nPrimitive call composition; no closed-form. The cart's value is the *choreography* of capability calls, not a numeric kernel.\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`meta/dm`** тАФ Meta Graph API messaging.\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Post one product across every Facebook Page you manage ┬╖ `meta-multi-page-product-post` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/meta-multi-page-product-post.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-stat