Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### 5 things to set up before you list ┬╖ `pink-before-listing-5-things` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-before-listing-5-things.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/listings`, `etsy/receipts`, `etsy/shop`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"About to list? The system noticed 5 things worth sorting first.\" It only wakes up when draft in progress happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/listings`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/shops/{shop_id}/listings`.\n- **`etsy/receipts`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 receipts.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Auto-blurb for the shop note тАФ seasonal, тЙд140 chars ┬╖ `pink-greeting-card-blurb` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-greeting-card-blurb.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Writes a warm, seasonal shop-note blurb right on your device тАФ no cloud needed.\" It only wakes up when listing viewed happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Listing completeness check тАФ local fix list ┬╖ `pink-listing-checklist` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-listing-checklist.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `etsy/listing`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Here are the things missing from this listing тАФ fix list, on-device.\" It only wakes up when listing selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It catches small problems early so they never become big ones.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nPrimitive call composition; no closed-form. The cart's value is the *choreography* of capability calls, not a numeric kernel.\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`etsy/listing`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/listings/{listing_id}`.\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Per-listing vitals ┬╖ 30-day trend ┬╖ percentile rank ┬╖ `pink-listing-dashboard-card` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-listing-dashboard-card.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `etsy/listing`, `etsy/listings`, `etsy/receipts`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"One card: this listing's vitals, 30-day trend, and percentile rank against your shop.\" It only wakes up when listing selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you put more polish on the words that decide whether a buyer clicks buy.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`etsy/listing`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/listings/{listing_id}`.\n- **`etsy/listings`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/shops/{shop_id}/listings`.\n- **`etsy/receipts`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 receipts.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Your morning 5 тАФ ranked actions across your shop ┬╖ `pink-morning-5-things` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-morning-5-things.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `ebay/listings`, `ebay/sold`, `etsy/listings`, `etsy/receipts`, `etsy/shop`, `loam/operator-state`, `meta/orders`, `model/fast`, `shopify/orders`, `shopify/products`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"First open of the day surfaces 5 ranked actions across all your connected surfaces.\" It only wakes up when app open happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`ebay/listings`** тАФ eBay Sell API `getInventoryItems`.\n- **`ebay/sold`** тАФ eBay Finding API тАФ also TeraPeak (Terapeak Product Research).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Capture your shop voice for future writing help ┬╖ `pink-onboarding-voice-ingest` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-onboarding-voice-ingest.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/listings`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Reads your past listing copy once and builds the voice corpus that powers future writing carts.\" It only wakes up when onboarding complete happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/listings`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/shops/{shop_id}/listings`.\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Cover-photo caption draft (on-device, photo features) ┬╖ `pink-photo-caption` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-photo-caption.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `model/fast`, `vision/label`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Draft a one-line caption from your cover photo's features тАФ all on device.\" It only wakes up when photo selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you ship cleaner-looking photos without spending a Saturday on them.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `vision/label` тАФ Multi-label tagging of an image (e.g., colours, materials, motifs).\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`vision/label`**: $\\{\\ell: P(\\ell \\mid I) > \\tau\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **`vision/label`** тАФ Google Cloud Vision `LABEL_DETECTION`; Hugging Face Florence-2.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Policy text rewrite in your voice ┬╖ `pink-policy-paraphrase` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-policy-paraphrase.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Paste a policy block тАФ get it back in your register, no marketing flatness.\" It only wakes up when policy rewrite requested happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### 5 things to do before you leave for vacation ┬╖ `pink-pre-vacation-5-things` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-pre-vacation-5-things.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Vacation marked тАФ here are 5 things to handle before you go.\" It only wakes up when vacation set happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Per-listing price history тАФ step-line view ┬╖ `pink-price-history-card` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-price-history-card.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `etsy/listing`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Every price change for this listing painted as a step-line, on-device.\" It only wakes up when listing selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you set prices that won't leave money on the table.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`etsy/listing`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/listings/{listing_id}`.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Talk to your shop тАФ plain-English search ┬╖ `pink-search-translate` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-search-translate.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Type 'show me my big yellow rings' тАФ the system finds matching listings on-device.\" It only wakes up when operator query happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps your listings get found by people actually searching for what you sell.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **`sakura/decide`** тАФ Reactive layer (Brooks 1986); same shape as the lowest layer of Simmons's Task Control Architecture.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Name this group of listings ┬╖ `pink-section-name-suggest` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-section-name-suggest.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Five or more listings selected тАФ here is a short, operator-voiced section title.\" It only wakes up when listings grouped happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you put more polish on the words that decide whether a buyer clicks buy.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Shop pulse тАФ live velocity canvas ┬╖ `pink-shop-pulse-card` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-shop-pulse-card.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Today's view and sale velocity painted as a living ambient canvas.\" It only wakes up when dashboard open happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`sakura/decide`** тАФ Reactive layer (Brooks 1986); same shape as the lowest layer of Simmons's Task Control Architecture.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Tag search тАФ listings using a tag and their performance ┬╖ `pink-tag-search-fold` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-tag-search-fold.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/remember`, `etsy/listings`, `etsy/receipts`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Type a tag тАФ see every listing using it and how each one performs.\" It only wakes up when tag search submitted happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps your listings get found by people actually searching for what you sell.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/listings`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/shops/{shop_id}/listings`.\n- **`etsy/receipts`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 receipts.\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Per-order thank-you note in your voice ┬╖ `pink-thank-you-note-draft` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-thank-you-note-draft.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"A new order arrived тАФ here is a thank-you note drafted in your voice.\" It only wakes up when order received happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Local title tightener тАФ shorten without losing the keyword ┬╖ `pink-title-tighten-local` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-title-tighten-local.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Shorten this title without losing the keyword тАФ тЙд80 chars, on-device.\" It only wakes up when listing selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps your listings get found by people actually searching for what you sell.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **`sakura/decide`** тАФ Reactive layer (Brooks 1986); same shape as the lowest layer of Simmons's Task Control Architecture.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Post-vacation recovery тАФ resume carts, reactivate ads, surge-watch ┬╖ `pink-vacation-mode-recovery` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/pink-vacation-mode-recovery.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Back from vacation тАФ the system noticed; carts resumed, ads queued, surge watch armed.\" It only wakes up when vacation end happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It catches small problems early so they never become big ones.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### PO Box detected тАФ carrier swap to postal service ┬╖ `po-box-incompatible-carrier` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/po-box-incompatible-carrier.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/receipts`, `loam/operator-state`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Ship-to is a PO Box тАФ private carriers will silent-fail; flag for postal routing.\" It only wakes up when order received happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/receipts`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 receipts.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Back-in-stock push alert to opted-in buyers ┬╖ `push-restock-alert` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/push-restock-alert.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/listing`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `pii/gate-status`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"A watched listing is back тАФ the system notifies opted-in buyers automatically.\" It only wakes up when listing restocked happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you know what to reorder before you run out тАФ and what's collecting dust.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`pii/gate-status`**: $g \\in \\{open, closed\\}, \\text{ default } closed$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/listing`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/listings/{listing_id}`.\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Restock after pack тАФ inventory decrement and reorder alert ┬╖ `restock-after-pack` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/restock-after-pack.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Packed a SKU? Inventory drops and you hear about it before you run dry.\" It only wakes up when pack confirmed happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you know what to reorder before you run out тАФ and what's collecting dust.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Buyer review PII redaction ┬╖ `review-pii-redact` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/review-pii-redact.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Strip names, addresses, and order numbers from buyer reviews before any public display.\" It only wakes up when review surface happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you stay on top of what buyers are actually saying.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nPrimitive call composition; no closed-form. The cart's value is the *choreography* of capability calls, not a numeric kernel.\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Review request at the carrier-optimal moment ┬╖ `review-solicit-post-delivery` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/review-solicit-post-delivery.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Tracking confirmed delivery тАФ surface the right moment to ask for a review.\" It only wakes up when delivery confirmed happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you stay on top of what buyers are actually saying.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Share a photo to every connected store in one step ┬╖ `share-photo-to-multi-store` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/share-photo-to-multi-store.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `ebay/update`, `etsy/upload-image`, `instagram/post`, `loam/operator-state`, `meta/marketplace`, `shopify/update`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"One photo, every connected storefront тАФ share in a single composition step.\" It only wakes up when photo selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you ship cleaner-looking photos without spending a Saturday on them.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity.\n\nWrite-class verbs are operator-gated тАФ the cart proposes; the operator approves with a tap.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`ebay/update`** тАФ eBay Sell API.\n- **`etsy/upload-image`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Set inventory across all Shopify locations for one SKU ┬╖ `shopify-multi-location-inventory-set` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/shopify-multi-location-inventory-set.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/remember`, `shopify/products`, `shopify/update`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Set absolute qty across multiple Shopify fulfillment locations for one SKU in one operation.\" It only wakes up when operator request happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you know what to reorder before you run out тАФ and what's collecting dust.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity.\n\nWrite-class verbs are operator-gated тАФ the cart proposes; the operator approves with a tap.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`shopify/products`** тАФ Shopify Admin API GraphQL.\n- **`shopify/update`** тАФ Shopify Admin API.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### UTM link builder for Shopify marketing ┬╖ `shopify-utm-builder` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/shopify-utm-builder.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `model/fast`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Build a UTM-tagged URL for any Shopify marketing activity тАФ copy and go.\" It only wakes up when shopify marketing activity happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### SMS opt-in collector with TCPA disclosures ┬╖ `sms-opt-in-collect` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/sms-opt-in-collect.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Surface a TCPA-shaped SMS opt-in with required disclosures at checkout and post-purchase.\" It only wakes up when checkout view happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### SMS STOP тАФ confirm unsubscribe within 24 h ┬╖ `sms-stop-honor` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/sms-stop-honor.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `model/fast`, `sakura/decide`, `sms/send`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Buyer texted STOP тАФ unsubscribe confirmed, opt-out recorded, compliance window honored.\" It only wakes up when sms inbound happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\nThis cart touches BUYER data so it gates on `pii/gate-status` per Lane-B5 ┬з6; defaults closed.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### New-supplier onboarding checklist ┬╖ `supplier-onboard-checklist` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/supplier-onboard-checklist.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `loam/operator-state`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Capture NET terms, EIN, contact, and holiday schedule for a new supplier тАФ one form, done.\" It only wakes up when form submit happens тАФ never when nothing's going on.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`cortex/recall`**: $\\text{recall}: (\\text{operator}, \\text{topic}, \\text{window}) \\mapsto \\text{fact} \\cup \\{\\bot\\}$\n- **`cortex/remember`**: $\\text{remember}: (\\text{slug}, \\text{topic}, \\text{shape}) \\to \\text{cortex} \\cup \\{f_t\\}$\n- **`loam/operator-state`**: $\\text{loam}: () \\to \\{vacation, paused, no\\text{-}new\\text{-}data, ok\\}$\n- **`sakura/decide`**: $d: (s, e) \\mapsto s'$ (small DFA transition)\n\n#### In the wild\n\n- **`cortex/recall`** тАФ Local key-value memory pattern; orchestration-framework memory modules and cloud-LLM `memory` features implement similar topic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`loam/operator-state`** тАФ Feature-flag gate (LaunchDarkly pattern); pre-flight condition guards in airline-flight-control software (DO-178C).\n- **`sakura/decide`** тАФ Reactive layer (Brooks 1986); same shape as the lowest layer of Simmons's Task Control Architecture.\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Incoming message triage тАФ tag before you read ┬╖ `ticket-triage-auto` ┬╖ Pink (Sakura local тАФ on-device)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/pink/ticket-triage-auto.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `cortex/recall`, `cortex/remember`, `etsy/conversations`, `loam/operator-state`, `sakura/decide`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"Each new message is tagged shipping, refund, product-question, complaint, or other тАФ locally, before you open it.\" It only wakes up when message received happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps your listings get found by people actually searching for what you sell.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `cortex/recall` тАФ Topic-keyed lookup against the local Cortex SQLite store. Returns the most recent fact tuple for `(operator, topic, window)` or null. Pure read; no LLM call. `cortex/remember` тАФ Append-only fact write to local Cortex with structured shape. Each write is a typed s-expression keyed by `(slug, topic, ts)`; durable record for replay/audit. See `curator-api/cortex_native_rs` for byte-identical RustтЖФPython parity. `sakura/decide` тАФ Local routing decision: given the cart's state and the incoming event, picks the next surface/state. Does not invoke an LLM.\n\nThis cart touches BUYER data so it gates on `pii/gate