opic-keyed recall.\n- **`cortex/remember`** тАФ Event-sourced state, Fowler (2005); SQLite WAL appends; CRDT-style local-first persistence per Kleppmann's *Designing Data-Intensive Applications* (2017).\n- **`etsy/listing`** тАФ Etsy Open API v3 `/listings/{listing_id}`.\n- **`model/fast`** тАФ Small-model-first routing тАФ see *Distilling Step-by-Step* (Hsieh et al. 2023).\n- **Category context** тАФ Klaviyo ($45/mo) and Yotpo ($79/mo) sell event-driven flows as their core product; Smile.io ($49/mo) covers loyalty events.\n\n---\n\n### Single-photo critique тАФ light, focus, composition ┬╖ `single-photo-critique` ┬╖ Green (cloud assist ┬╖ vision ┬╖ web)\n\n**Dir:** `curator-web/src/scheme/carts/imagine/single-photo-critique.sks`\n**Verbs called:** `model/fast`, `vision/label`\n**Wired:** yes\n\n#### Layperson\n\nWhen this fires, Sakura tells you: \"One photo in тАФ plain-language critique out in seconds.\" It only wakes up when photo selected happens тАФ never when nothing's going on. It helps you ship cleaner-looking photos without spending a Saturday on them.\n\n#### CS / engineering / math\n\nEvery Curator cart is a tiny state machine implemented in Scheme тАФ the `(cart ...)` form declares cadence, tier, and PII class; the body is a sequence of `(define (state ctx) ...)` functions, each returning `next`, `wait`, `after`, `escalate`, or `done`. The state-machine spine (precondition_fetch тЖТ guard тЖТ act тЖТ result тЖТ on_error{retry|degrade|escalate|ask_human}) is the same shape across all 860 carts тАФ see [[project_curator_state_machine_spine]] and `curator-web/src/scheme/runtime/` for the engine.\n\nThe technique-bearing calls are: `model/fast` тАФ Capability-verb call: low-latency on-device classifier-style call. Used for tone / sentiment / categorize. `vision/label` тАФ Multi-label tagging of an image (e.g., colours, materials, motifs).\n\n#### Principle / equation\n\nDrivers of this cart, expressed formally:\n\n- **`vision/label`**: $\\{\\ell: P(\\ell \\